About 60,000 tonnes of harvestedraw cotton may be spoiled by rain in Tanzania's northernShinyanga region because it is stored in the open or in crudevillage sheds, radio Tanzania reported.    The cotton, worth one billion shillings, cannot be moved toginneries in the region because most mill warehouses are full.Many mills are not working because of a lack of spare parts, itadded.    Agriculture Ministry officials have forecast a 1987/88cotton harvest of about 200,000 tonnes, down from 215,000 in1986/87. REUTER&#3;